 <datafield tag="245" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
  <subfield code="a">$2d\,$ Fu–Kane–Mele invariant as Wess–Zumino action of the sewing matrix</subfield>
  <subfield code="9">Springer</subfield>
 </datafield>
 <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
  <subfield code="a">We show that the Fu–Kane–Mele invariant of the 2d time-reversal invariant crystalline insulators is equal to the properly normalized Wess–Zumino action of the so-called sewing-matrix field defined on the Brillouin torus. Applied to 3d, the result permits a direct proof of the known relation between the strong Fu–Kane–Mele invariant and the Chern–Simons action of the non-Abelian Berry connection on the bundle of valence states.</subfield>
  <subfield code="9">Springer</subfield>
 </datafield>
